  "original_title": "\u0d87\u0db8\u0dd9\u0dbb\u0dd2\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dd4 \u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db8\u0dd2\u0d9a \u0d85\u0d82\u0dc1\u0dba \u0dc0\u0dc3\u0dbb \u0daf\u0dd9\u0d9a\u0d9a \u0d85\u0dc0\u0db8 \u0db8\u0da7\u0dca\u0da7\u0db8\u0d9a",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The US industrial sector is at a two-year low",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "U.S. manufacturing activity slowed more than expected in June, hitting its lowest level for the first time in two years amid aggressive monetary policy tightened by the Federal Reserve as new orders contracted.",
        "A survey by the Institute for Supply Management (ISM) on Friday showed a downward gauge of factory employment contracts for the second month in a row, although an \"overwhelming majority\" of firms showed they were hiring.",
        "\"This doesn't mean there's a recession yet, but growth conditions are easing broadly in response to Fed policy rate tightening and prolonged cost pressures for consumers and businesses,\" said Ben Ayers, senior economist at Nationwide in Columbus, Ohio.",
        "The ISM survey's index of national factory activity fell to 53.0 last month. The figure is the lowest since June 2020, when the sector recovered from a Covid-19 downturn. It was recorded at 56.1 in May. However, the index would need to fall to 43.1 to signal a recession."
      ],
